As private capital has no social responsibility and therefore no responsibility for the unemployment it causes, public expenditure is necessarily increasing.
This situation is reinforced by the fact that the entrepreneurs are absolutely unwilling to pay their taxes and thus to replace the social and economic damage they cause.
