This is expressed in particular in amendments to existing laws.
The aim of these measures is to force one's own population to accept the dictate of private capital, particularly in the field of wages.
This is done, on the one hand, by economic constraints on long-term unemployment and, on the other, by the reduction of workers' rights.
The result is growing poverty, as well as increasing differences between the poor and the rich.
In Germany, there have been public food outlets for poor people for some years now, who are no longer able to feed through their own work.
