As it turns out, today's society, as well as in ancient times, is based on the ruthless preference of its own advantage, without paying attention to the interests of society as a whole.
Private capital is, by its very nature, not in a position to recognize and enforce the advantage for the whole of society.
The result, today as at the time, is an unprecedented decadence of the elites, who do not in the least seek deeper reforms.
